<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>How to Use Our Timetable Generator</h1>
        <p>Creating your personalized weekly timetable is easy! Follow these simple steps to get started:</p>

        <h2>Step 1: Define Your Weekly Structure</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Enter Your Working Days:</strong>
                On the initial screen, you'll find a field for "Working Days."
                Enter a number between <strong>1 and 7</strong> (e.g., '5' for a standard Monday-Friday schedule).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Specify Subjects Per Day:</strong>
                Next, input the "Subjects per Day." This represents the number of periods or slots you have each working day.
                Enter a positive number <strong>less than 9</strong> (e.g., '4' for four periods daily).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Indicate Total Subjects:</strong>
                Finally, enter the "Total Subjects" you need to schedule for the entire week.
                This should be a <strong>positive number</strong> (e.g., '4' if you have Gujarati, English, Science, and Maths).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Review Total Hours:</strong>
                As you enter these values, the <strong>"Total hours for week"</strong> will automatically calculate. This is the total number of available slots in your timetable.
                Ensure these details look correct, then click the <strong>"Submit"</strong> button to proceed.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Step 2: Allocate Hours for Each Subject</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Subject Hour Input:</strong>
                After submission, a new form will appear, listing each of your subjects (e.g., "Gujarati," "English," "Science," "Maths").
                For each subject, enter the total number of hours (periods) you want to dedicate to it <strong>over the entire week</strong>.
                <div class="note">
                    <strong>For example:</strong> If "Total hours for week" is 20, you might enter: Gujarati 3, English 4, Science 6, Maths 7 (total 20).
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Match Total Hours:</strong>
                <strong>Important:</strong> The sum of all the hours you enter for your subjects *must exactly equal* the <strong>"Total hours for week"</strong> calculated in Step 1.
                The system will guide you if there's a mismatch. Adjust your subject hours until the total matches.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Enable Generation:</strong>
                Once your subject hours add up correctly, the <strong>"Generate"</strong> button will become enabled.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Step 3: Generate Your Timetable!</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Click "Generate":</strong>
                With the "Generate" button enabled, simply click it.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>View Your Timetable:</strong>
                The system will instantly create and display your personalized weekly timetable!
                You'll see a clear grid with your subjects dynamically placed across your working days and periods.
            </li>
        </ul>

    </div>
</body>
